Package attTester

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AHRSBenchTest  
    AHRSPlayBack  
    AHRSRealTime  
    AttComm
    This class sends a command to the AHRS to send an attitude data packet.
    AttRecv
    Retrieves the buffered data from the RS232 serial port, decodes the data (which comes in IEEE-754 format) into the appropriate values (roll, pitch, and heading in degrees).
    ConnectMySQL
    This class acts as an interface to the MySQL database for creating tables, loading tables, and retrieving the data from tables.
    ConnectTextData  
    DataStore  
    DecodeAttitude
    Decodes the attitude data packet (byte array) for each AHRS model.
    Thread_Queue
    This is the thread-safe communications link between AHRSRealTime (which loops while receiving the AHRS data and sending it to the graphics objects) and AttRecv.
    ThreadQueueCmd
    This is the thread-safe communications link between the AttGraphicsContainer (contains the GUI elements for setting up and running the simulation) and AttComm (sends the data packet request to the AHRS).
    ThreadQueueRcv
    This is the thread-safe communications link between the AttGraphicsContainer (contains the GUI elements for setting up and running the simulation) and AttRecv (receives and processes the AHRS data packet).
    TwoWaySerialComm
    Initializes the serial communications and launches two threads â€“ AttCom and AttRecv.
